\title{join topology}
\taxon{definition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\import{macros01}
\cite{maclane-moerdijk-1994}{Mac Lane & Moerdijk}{p. 114}

\p{The \em{join topology} on a [complete](rs-006O) [Heyting
algebra](rs-006V) is the [Grothendieck topology](rs-0079) generated by the
[basis](rs-007A) of families #{\{x_i\leq x\}} such that #{\Join x_i = x}.}

